WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:45.400


00:00:58.652 --> 00:01:03.076
[Episode 13: Between Cool and Passion]

00:01:05.693 --> 00:01:06.730
So?

00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:08.029
What happened?

00:01:08.029 --> 00:01:10.654
So I asked...

00:01:10.654 --> 00:01:14.047
"Then why was the dragon there
in the first place?"

00:01:14.047 --> 00:01:15.238
"I mean, it's not like..."

00:01:15.238 --> 00:01:18.904
"a dragon just flies around for no reason,
right?"

00:01:18.904 --> 00:01:22.046
They said,
"The sky looked empty, so I just added one."

00:01:22.046 --> 00:01:23.279
Can you believe that?

00:01:23.279 --> 00:01:25.838
They're always like that. Seriously.

00:01:25.838 --> 00:01:27.488
And when they get called out, they're like,
"What did I do wrong?"

00:01:27.488 --> 00:01:29.863
For someone in low-power mode,

00:01:29.863 --> 00:01:32.263
this is how you survive a team dinner.

00:01:36.196 --> 00:01:40.055
You stop thinking.

00:01:40.738 --> 00:01:43.191
Let's just rest.

00:01:46.154 --> 00:01:48.154
Trying to conserve energy,

00:01:48.154 --> 00:01:50.667
the village stays dim,

00:01:51.696 --> 00:01:54.662
and kind of lifeless.

00:01:57.322 --> 00:01:59.389
It's cold.

00:02:01.196 --> 00:02:04.236
What do you think, PD Shin?

00:02:05.613 --> 00:02:07.855
Not sure.

00:02:07.855 --> 00:02:08.916
That's it?

00:02:08.916 --> 00:02:12.160
Nothing really comes to mind.

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:15.522
- Oh my, that's cold.
- So cold.

00:02:15.522 --> 00:02:18.989
People call that "cold."

00:02:18.989 --> 00:02:23.482
It's rare for passion to spark.

00:02:25.279 --> 00:02:27.518
But...

00:02:27.518 --> 00:02:29.238
- PD Shin.
- Yes?

00:02:29.238 --> 00:02:30.988
You can head out first.

00:02:30.988 --> 00:02:33.071
- Sorry?
- We're going to...

00:02:33.071 --> 00:02:36.284
look around and grab lunch.

00:02:37.307 --> 00:02:39.738
- Then I'll...
- No, it's fine.

00:02:39.738 --> 00:02:42.464
- No, I'll make the reservation.
- No.

00:02:43.438 --> 00:02:46.411
We'll take care of it.

00:02:48.036 --> 00:02:50.409
You can go.

00:02:51.313 --> 00:02:52.863
Okay.

00:02:52.863 --> 00:02:54.949
See you later.

00:02:57.334 --> 00:02:59.987
I don't like that.

00:03:10.154 --> 00:03:11.988
No sense of boundaries.

00:03:11.988 --> 00:03:15.339
All that matters is how he feels.

00:03:22.196 --> 00:03:23.488
Hello.

00:03:23.488 --> 00:03:26.481
I really don't like that.

00:03:30.363 --> 00:03:33.676
Whatever. Not my problem.

00:04:00.307 --> 00:04:01.647
Wait, is that a fire?

00:04:01.647 --> 00:04:03.022
What is that?

00:04:03.022 --> 00:04:05.762
I didn't light anything.

00:04:12.045 --> 00:04:14.464
It's warm.

00:04:16.345 --> 00:04:18.811
They spent the whole day together
and he just got in.

00:04:18.811 --> 00:04:21.739
Is this thing actually happening?

00:04:21.739 --> 00:04:22.848
I'm telling you,

00:04:22.848 --> 00:04:26.321
he is absolutely giddy.

00:04:26.321 --> 00:04:28.578
Is that so?

00:04:33.029 --> 00:04:36.222
This is so annoying.

00:04:37.154 --> 00:04:41.529
The only time someone
in low-power mode burns up

00:04:41.529 --> 00:04:44.528
isn't when they like someone,

00:04:44.528 --> 00:04:47.196
it's when they don't.

00:04:47.196 --> 00:04:50.154
But honestly,
don't they seem like a pretty good match?

00:04:50.154 --> 00:04:51.571
Not really.

00:04:51.571 --> 00:04:53.730
What?

00:04:53.730 --> 00:04:55.263
I don't think they go together that well.

00:04:55.263 --> 00:04:57.411
Not a match? Why not? I think they'd be great.

00:04:57.411 --> 00:04:59.279
No,

00:04:59.279 --> 00:05:01.063
they're not a match.

00:05:01.063 --> 00:05:03.350
[Writer Kim Ju Ho]

00:05:04.563 --> 00:05:07.105
What now?

00:05:10.610 --> 00:05:11.638
Hello.

00:05:11.638 --> 00:05:13.321
Hey, PD Shin.

00:05:13.321 --> 00:05:16.031
You left with Writer Kim, right?

00:05:16.821 --> 00:05:18.859
Yeah, so what?

00:05:18.859 --> 00:05:21.207
Yes, since it's dark...

00:05:22.321 --> 00:05:25.238
She's still up, right?

00:05:25.238 --> 00:05:27.488
But she isn't picking up.

00:05:27.488 --> 00:05:32.613
Bring Writer Kim and come here.

00:05:32.613 --> 00:05:34.808
Sorry?

00:05:34.808 --> 00:05:36.835
What a boomer.

00:05:37.692 --> 00:05:40.020
I seriously hate him.

00:05:42.946 --> 00:05:45.279
She can't come.

00:05:45.279 --> 00:05:47.654
What? How come?

00:05:47.654 --> 00:05:51.488
She said she'd watch a movie, so we came.

00:05:51.488 --> 00:05:54.029
It just started, so two more hours.

00:05:54.029 --> 00:05:56.571
- What?
- Wait, hold on.

00:05:56.571 --> 00:05:58.063
That's a lie.

00:05:58.063 --> 00:05:59.113
What movie?

00:05:59.113 --> 00:06:01.100
So don't call her.

00:06:01.100 --> 00:06:03.821
She won't pick up.

00:06:03.821 --> 00:06:06.321
Wait, Soon Rok. You sure about this?

00:06:06.321 --> 00:06:07.894
Yes.

00:06:09.238 --> 00:06:11.698
Yes, understood.

00:06:14.896 --> 00:06:18.688
You don't need to butt in like this.

00:06:18.688 --> 00:06:19.904
Who is that?

00:06:19.904 --> 00:06:22.071
I'm the only one awake.

00:06:22.071 --> 00:06:25.037
Who the hell is doing this?

00:06:33.156 --> 00:06:35.946
Emotion Cell, what are you doing up?

00:06:35.946 --> 00:06:37.363
I'm building a fire.

00:06:37.363 --> 00:06:40.189
What? Why?

00:06:41.855 --> 00:06:44.388
No, don't do anything pointless.

00:06:44.388 --> 00:06:46.990
I just hate that guy.

00:06:48.855 --> 00:06:50.738
Hey, let go!

00:06:50.738 --> 00:06:53.526
I said no!

00:06:53.526 --> 00:06:55.992
Hold it in!

00:07:05.946 --> 00:07:09.988
"Want to watch the movie together?"

00:07:10.686 --> 00:07:13.904
What is that?

00:07:13.904 --> 00:07:17.139
You said solo's easier.

00:07:18.322 --> 00:07:22.022
No, wait, Soon Rok.

00:07:22.022 --> 00:07:25.363
[Want to watch the movie together?]
[You said solo's easier]

00:07:25.363 --> 00:07:28.402
Want to watch together?

00:07:30.647 --> 00:07:33.272
I'll head over now.

00:07:34.221 --> 00:07:36.789
I'll be there in ten.

00:07:39.821 --> 00:07:42.711
I'll grab the tickets.

00:07:44.547 --> 00:07:47.363
This is so not like you, Soon Rok.

00:07:47.363 --> 00:07:50.238
Why are you butting in?

00:07:50.238 --> 00:07:53.071
She wants to see the movie too.

00:07:53.071 --> 00:07:56.064
She said she did.

00:08:00.149 --> 00:08:03.149
Oh, there it is.

00:08:15.779 --> 00:08:20.032
What? Did Writer Kim get here already?

00:08:22.654 --> 00:08:25.238
What is this?

00:08:25.238 --> 00:08:27.938
What the hell is this?

00:08:27.938 --> 00:08:30.522
This is bad.

00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:51.817
Writer Kim!

00:08:58.994 --> 00:09:02.613
What do you want to drink?

00:09:02.613 --> 00:09:05.179
Coffee? Coke?

00:09:08.296 --> 00:09:11.904
Since it's late, Coke sounds better, right?

00:09:11.904 --> 00:09:13.480
Hey, let's get one more Coke.

00:09:13.480 --> 00:09:14.615
Okay.

00:09:14.615 --> 00:09:17.155
One more Coke, please.

00:09:20.368 --> 00:09:21.730
I came too.

00:09:21.730 --> 00:09:23.891
Heard you were seeing a movie.

00:09:23.891 --> 00:09:26.738
I actually wanted to see it anyway,

00:09:26.738 --> 00:09:28.738
so I rushed over.

00:09:28.738 --> 00:09:31.778
Good thing it hasn't started yet.

00:09:32.488 --> 00:09:33.779
What?

00:09:33.779 --> 00:09:36.050
Wait, what is this?

00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:38.113
I think Writer Kim Ju Ho told him

00:09:38.113 --> 00:09:40.429
to text Yumi.

00:09:40.429 --> 00:09:41.863
No way.

00:09:41.863 --> 00:09:43.279
I think that's it.

00:09:43.279 --> 00:09:46.363
He figured Yumi wouldn't show up.

00:09:51.441 --> 00:09:54.200
What the...

00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:58.113
Are you guys kidding me?

00:10:03.488 --> 00:10:04.571
I see.

00:10:04.571 --> 00:10:06.238
Actually, we were just

00:10:06.238 --> 00:10:08.904
thinking about going for another round,

00:10:08.904 --> 00:10:10.529
but a movie sounds better.

00:10:10.529 --> 00:10:13.502
I'm into the arts too.

00:10:16.113 --> 00:10:17.946
I see.

00:10:17.946 --> 00:10:20.321
Hey, which theater is it?

00:10:20.321 --> 00:10:22.321
Is it that way?

00:10:22.321 --> 00:10:24.306
Yes.

00:10:24.306 --> 00:10:26.696
Writer Kim, this way.

00:10:26.696 --> 00:10:29.003
Let's go.

00:10:48.196 --> 00:10:50.084
Excuse me.

00:10:50.084 --> 00:10:52.321
Here.

00:10:52.321 --> 00:10:54.809
- Here.
- Thank you.

00:10:58.272 --> 00:11:00.980
Watching a movie in Busan feels kind of new.

00:11:00.980 --> 00:11:02.294
It brings back memories.

00:11:02.294 --> 00:11:03.308
Yeah.

00:11:04.946 --> 00:11:08.529
When I came to Busan for a baseball game,

00:11:08.529 --> 00:11:10.446
I did not want to go home,

00:11:10.446 --> 00:11:14.456
so I watched a movie and took the train after.

00:11:15.654 --> 00:11:17.347
I see.

00:11:45.937 --> 00:11:47.558
Oh my.

00:11:49.136 --> 00:11:51.613
It is funnier than I expected.

00:11:51.613 --> 00:11:54.113
This is good. I thought it would be serious.

00:11:54.113 --> 00:11:55.313
I will step out first.

00:11:55.313 --> 00:11:56.923
I need the restroom.

00:11:56.923 --> 00:11:59.151
Sure.

00:12:04.150 --> 00:12:05.321
PD Shin.

00:12:05.321 --> 00:12:06.988
Where should we go next?

00:12:06.988 --> 00:12:08.230
Sorry?

00:12:08.230 --> 00:12:09.279
"Next?"

00:12:09.279 --> 00:12:11.696
It feels too early to call it a night.

00:12:11.696 --> 00:12:14.779
I don't think she will want a bar,

00:12:14.779 --> 00:12:16.321
so maybe we grab some beers

00:12:16.321 --> 00:12:19.394
and take a walk by the beach?

00:12:24.143 --> 00:12:26.779
I told you not to butt in.

00:12:26.779 --> 00:12:28.238
What is this?

00:12:28.238 --> 00:12:31.738
This happened because you lit that fire.

00:12:31.738 --> 00:12:34.149
I didn't light it.

00:12:34.149 --> 00:12:35.654
It is your campfire.

00:12:35.654 --> 00:12:37.546
If not you, then who?

00:12:37.546 --> 00:12:38.904
I don't know.

00:12:38.904 --> 00:12:41.863
When I woke up, it was already burning.

00:12:41.863 --> 00:12:44.509
That makes no sense.

00:12:44.509 --> 00:12:46.001
Just go to sleep.

00:12:46.001 --> 00:12:48.901
I don't even have the energy to argue.

00:12:59.154 --> 00:13:01.488
Yumi, let it go today.

00:13:01.488 --> 00:13:03.774
It's too late.

00:13:12.821 --> 00:13:15.147
Oh, Writer Kim.

00:13:15.147 --> 00:13:16.904
Would you like a beer?

00:13:16.904 --> 00:13:19.221
We can get some fresh air by the beach.

00:13:19.221 --> 00:13:21.357
Writer Kim.

00:13:22.029 --> 00:13:25.071
Do you like me?

00:13:25.071 --> 00:13:26.571
- Sorry?
- I really hate guys

00:13:26.571 --> 00:13:28.988
who sneak up like this,

00:13:28.988 --> 00:13:31.738
playing it off like a joke.

00:13:31.738 --> 00:13:34.738
Maybe you think that works on women,

00:13:34.738 --> 00:13:36.779
but it doesn't work on me.

00:13:36.779 --> 00:13:38.772
You keep using PD Shin as an excuse,

00:13:38.772 --> 00:13:41.613
then sending him away halfway through.

00:13:41.613 --> 00:13:44.414
Isn't that a bit outdated?

00:13:46.279 --> 00:13:47.785
Oh, no.

00:13:47.785 --> 00:13:49.376
Is that how you saw it?

00:13:49.376 --> 00:13:50.404
That's not...

00:13:50.404 --> 00:13:52.738
I asked if you like me.

00:13:52.738 --> 00:13:53.904
Do you have feelings for me?

00:13:53.904 --> 00:13:56.831
Do you want something with me?

00:13:57.863 --> 00:14:00.238
Why not just be honest?

00:14:00.238 --> 00:14:02.488
You always talk about "our generation."

00:14:02.488 --> 00:14:04.196
Yeah, we're old enough.

00:14:04.196 --> 00:14:06.446
We know what we're doing, right?

00:14:06.446 --> 00:14:09.363
Yeah. Right.

00:14:09.363 --> 00:14:11.113
So you like me?

00:14:11.113 --> 00:14:14.139
And you want to see where this goes?

00:14:17.154 --> 00:14:18.654
Yes.

00:14:18.654 --> 00:14:21.371
I'd like to see where things go with you.

00:14:21.371 --> 00:14:24.071
I see.

00:14:24.071 --> 00:14:26.196
But

00:14:26.196 --> 00:14:28.113
I'm not interested.

00:14:28.113 --> 00:14:29.154
- Sorry?
- I don't want

00:14:29.154 --> 00:14:31.113
to see you outside of work.

00:14:31.113 --> 00:14:35.654
So please don't do this again.

00:14:35.654 --> 00:14:38.238
And PD Shin,

00:14:38.238 --> 00:14:40.654
is this part of your job?

00:14:40.654 --> 00:14:43.613
Do you usually handle things like this
for your writers?

00:14:43.613 --> 00:14:47.279
This isn't work. It's overstepping.

00:14:47.279 --> 00:14:50.654
Doing this doesn't make you a better PD.

00:14:50.654 --> 00:14:53.625
It really doesn't.

00:14:56.571 --> 00:14:58.779
Thanks for the movie.

00:14:58.779 --> 00:15:00.029
Since it was on you,

00:15:00.029 --> 00:15:03.238
I'll get you both coffee tomorrow.

00:15:03.238 --> 00:15:06.391
I should go. See you tomorrow.

00:15:18.738 --> 00:15:21.431
Did I just get rejected?

00:15:24.904 --> 00:15:28.613
She just shut me down like that?

00:15:28.613 --> 00:15:29.738
That was...

00:15:29.738 --> 00:15:32.444
She totally slammed the door on me.

00:15:37.740 --> 00:15:40.113
That was unbelievable, seriously.

00:15:40.113 --> 00:15:42.279
Good.

00:15:42.279 --> 00:15:45.238
I thought he was decent,
but how can he play with people like that?

00:15:45.238 --> 00:15:46.446
That was perfect.

00:15:46.446 --> 00:15:48.529
You had to say it.

00:15:49.307 --> 00:15:50.988
Beats me.

00:15:50.988 --> 00:15:52.613
I'm done.

00:15:52.613 --> 00:15:54.113
Just forget it.

00:15:54.113 --> 00:15:57.226
Yeah. Let's just drop it.

00:16:25.029 --> 00:16:27.249
- Thanks.
- Bye.

00:16:32.379 --> 00:16:34.272
Excuse me, where are the umbrellas?

00:16:34.272 --> 00:16:37.259
We just sold the last one.

00:17:08.363 --> 00:17:11.321
Emotion Cell, there you are.

00:17:11.321 --> 00:17:13.029
What are you doing?

00:17:13.029 --> 00:17:15.696
You were all fired up earlier...

00:17:15.696 --> 00:17:17.363
I feel sad.

00:17:17.363 --> 00:17:21.779
I actually felt something
for Soon Rok for once.

00:17:21.779 --> 00:17:25.579
I was really excited. It's been a while.

00:17:26.271 --> 00:17:28.604
Don't cry.

00:18:06.475 --> 00:18:08.238
Writer Kim.

00:18:08.238 --> 00:18:10.702
There you are.

00:18:11.696 --> 00:18:14.742
I saw it pouring and came after you.

00:18:15.988 --> 00:18:17.654
You don't even have an umbrella.

00:18:17.654 --> 00:18:19.135
Why follow me?

00:18:19.135 --> 00:18:21.571
I was going to buy you one.

00:18:21.571 --> 00:18:25.374
They're sold out.

00:18:25.374 --> 00:18:28.171
So I'm just standing here too.

00:18:30.446 --> 00:18:32.406
Oh, okay.

00:18:50.404 --> 00:18:53.977
There should be another store nearby.

00:19:08.071 --> 00:19:10.371
About earlier...

00:19:11.757 --> 00:19:13.634
I'm sorry.

00:19:16.029 --> 00:19:19.488
I wasn't in a great mood.

00:19:19.488 --> 00:19:21.847
I don't think he meant any harm, but...

00:19:30.404 --> 00:19:32.154
No.

00:19:32.154 --> 00:19:34.530
You were cool.

00:19:36.446 --> 00:19:37.972
What?

00:19:40.420 --> 00:19:42.417
You were so cool.

00:20:02.284 --> 00:20:05.154
There's a convenience store over there.

00:20:05.154 --> 00:20:07.363
Wait here for a second.

00:20:22.980 --> 00:20:26.660
[Episode 14: Soon Rok's Principles]

00:20:43.488 --> 00:20:45.654
Soon Rok,

00:20:45.654 --> 00:20:48.446
why did you say that just now?

00:20:48.446 --> 00:20:51.154
Calling Writer Kim cool...

00:20:51.154 --> 00:20:54.363
Are you sure that was okay?

00:20:54.363 --> 00:20:58.368
Feels like a rule violation.

00:21:07.820 --> 00:21:09.196
Do you have umbrellas here?

00:21:09.196 --> 00:21:10.904
- Over there.
- Thanks.

00:21:10.904 --> 00:21:13.724
Wait, this won't work.

00:21:14.562 --> 00:21:17.509
Emergency power, on!

00:21:23.515 --> 00:21:25.071
What?

00:21:25.988 --> 00:21:28.029
What is that?

00:21:28.871 --> 00:21:32.647
Why are you waking us up?

00:21:32.647 --> 00:21:34.988
We can't just ignore this.

00:21:34.988 --> 00:21:38.381
Bring me Kim Yumi's chart. Now.

00:21:40.337 --> 00:21:41.363
Here.

00:21:41.363 --> 00:21:43.196
Name, Kim Yumi.

00:21:43.196 --> 00:21:44.869
Occupation, writer.

00:21:44.869 --> 00:21:47.696
Relationship, work.

00:21:47.696 --> 00:21:49.696
Priority, high.

00:21:49.696 --> 00:21:52.115
Closeness, low.

00:21:52.115 --> 00:21:53.904
Affinity, average.

00:21:53.904 --> 00:21:55.196
See?

00:21:55.196 --> 00:21:57.904
There's nothing special here. Just work.

00:21:57.904 --> 00:22:01.029
She's just one of the writers under contract.

00:22:01.029 --> 00:22:03.446
He's not even assigned to her right now.

00:22:03.446 --> 00:22:06.571
So was his actions today appropriate?

00:22:06.571 --> 00:22:08.363
Did he follow the rules?

00:22:08.363 --> 00:22:10.738
Soon Rok's Principle one.

00:22:10.738 --> 00:22:11.863
Writer Kim,

00:22:11.863 --> 00:22:14.446
want to watch the movie together?

00:22:14.446 --> 00:22:16.363
He doesn't go to the movies alone

00:22:16.363 --> 00:22:19.696
with someone he doesn't have feelings for.

00:22:19.696 --> 00:22:21.279
Soon Rok's Principle two.

00:22:21.279 --> 00:22:23.206
You were so cool.

00:22:23.206 --> 00:22:27.696
He doesn't evaluate a writer
on anything but their work.

00:22:27.696 --> 00:22:31.013
He broke two core principles.

00:22:31.013 --> 00:22:32.196
All because

00:22:32.196 --> 00:22:34.849
Emotion Cell lost control.

00:22:34.849 --> 00:22:37.450
Emotion Cell? Seriously?

00:22:37.450 --> 00:22:39.446
I told you, I didn't start the fire.

00:22:39.446 --> 00:22:41.821
Either way, the rules were broken.

00:22:41.821 --> 00:22:45.432
She's just a work contact.

00:22:51.571 --> 00:22:52.821
Is there only one umbrella?

00:22:52.821 --> 00:22:55.238
Yes, that's the last one.

00:23:08.571 --> 00:23:11.031
Let's wrap this up.

00:23:11.988 --> 00:23:15.147
Is he close enough
to watch a movie alone with Writer?

00:23:15.147 --> 00:23:16.196
No.

00:23:16.196 --> 00:23:18.863
Is he close enough to call her cool?

00:23:18.863 --> 00:23:19.904
No.

00:23:19.904 --> 00:23:22.696
Is he close enough to share an umbrella?

00:23:22.696 --> 00:23:24.586
No.

00:23:33.821 --> 00:23:35.404
Conclusion.

00:23:35.404 --> 00:23:38.674
We don't cross the line anymore.

00:23:42.238 --> 00:23:44.983
How far did he go?

00:23:56.028 --> 00:23:58.838
That looks like Soon Rok.

00:24:02.588 --> 00:24:05.022
It's Soon Rok!

00:24:12.401 --> 00:24:14.511
Writer Kim.

00:24:15.404 --> 00:24:16.779
Where did you go?

00:24:16.779 --> 00:24:20.059
They only had one umbrella there too.

00:24:22.546 --> 00:24:23.696
Take this.

00:24:23.696 --> 00:24:25.071
What about you?

00:24:25.071 --> 00:24:26.988
I'm already soaked.

00:24:26.988 --> 00:24:29.196
I should get back to Writer Kim Ju Ho.

00:24:29.196 --> 00:24:31.108
But...

00:24:34.404 --> 00:24:37.516
I'll get going.

00:24:39.529 --> 00:24:41.476
Wait...

00:24:49.876 --> 00:24:51.904
Alright, that settles it.

00:24:51.904 --> 00:24:53.696
Emergency over.

00:24:53.696 --> 00:24:56.289
Wait, look behind him!

00:25:18.446 --> 00:25:21.824
I can't just take this by myself.

00:25:21.824 --> 00:25:24.863
We can go to the hotel and borrow an umbrella.

00:25:24.863 --> 00:25:26.821
Come on.

00:25:26.821 --> 00:25:28.654
What now?

00:25:28.654 --> 00:25:30.446
What's he going to do?

00:25:30.446 --> 00:25:32.863
What if she asks to share?

00:25:32.863 --> 00:25:35.321
In that case...

00:25:35.321 --> 00:25:38.654
That's not in his rulebook.

00:25:46.363 --> 00:25:47.571
What is this?

00:25:47.571 --> 00:25:49.113
Why is he walking so far away?

00:25:49.113 --> 00:25:51.404
Is he seriously keeping his distance?

00:25:51.404 --> 00:25:52.946
Come closer.

00:25:52.946 --> 00:25:54.245
You're getting soaked.

00:25:54.245 --> 00:25:57.959
I'm already soaked, so it's fine.

00:26:17.580 --> 00:26:18.613
Oh my.

00:26:18.613 --> 00:26:19.904
What is this now?

00:26:19.904 --> 00:26:22.324
This is like a drama.

00:26:22.324 --> 00:26:24.654
I'll hold the umbrella.

00:26:24.654 --> 00:26:25.779
Okay.

00:26:25.779 --> 00:26:27.987
Let's go.

00:26:29.135 --> 00:26:31.188
This way.

00:26:31.188 --> 00:26:33.095
Okay.

00:26:54.779 --> 00:26:57.029
Do you think

00:26:57.029 --> 00:26:59.654
he's really upset?

00:26:59.654 --> 00:27:02.484
You don't have to worry about it.

00:27:03.404 --> 00:27:06.779
Still, it's hard not to worry at all.

00:27:06.779 --> 00:27:08.279
You said what you needed to say.

00:27:08.279 --> 00:27:11.232
You really don't have to worry.

00:27:24.946 --> 00:27:26.488
A Maltese!

00:27:26.488 --> 00:27:27.863
Isn't that a Maltese?

00:27:27.863 --> 00:27:29.154
This one?

00:27:29.154 --> 00:27:32.071
Yeah, it is.

00:27:32.071 --> 00:27:34.029
I thought you didn't like Maltese.

00:27:34.029 --> 00:27:36.279
Why do you have a picture of one?

00:27:36.279 --> 00:27:38.154
That's my dog.

00:27:38.154 --> 00:27:39.946
Kongsoon.

00:27:39.946 --> 00:27:43.659
My parents take care of her now,
so I don't see her much.

00:27:44.972 --> 00:27:46.279
But I don't think

00:27:46.279 --> 00:27:51.041
I ever said I don't like Maltese.

00:27:51.041 --> 00:27:53.321
No, I'm pretty sure you did...

00:27:53.321 --> 00:27:55.613
You said it that time.

00:27:55.613 --> 00:27:56.946
Yeah.

00:27:56.946 --> 00:27:58.988
By any chance...

00:27:58.988 --> 00:28:01.904
do you not like dogs?

00:28:01.904 --> 00:28:04.738
You asked if I was scared or had allergies,

00:28:04.738 --> 00:28:06.696
and I said not really.

00:28:06.696 --> 00:28:08.179
No, not really.

00:28:08.179 --> 00:28:11.238
Oh, that's a relief.

00:28:11.238 --> 00:28:14.849
Then could you pet her?

00:28:16.218 --> 00:28:19.196
You want me to?

00:28:19.196 --> 00:28:21.363
But you didn't even want to pet her...

00:28:21.363 --> 00:28:22.779
I thought she might bite.

00:28:22.779 --> 00:28:23.946
My Kongsoon...

00:28:23.946 --> 00:28:27.209
she bites strangers sometimes.

00:28:28.029 --> 00:28:29.654
But Maltese

00:28:29.654 --> 00:28:30.946
aren't that smart.

00:28:30.946 --> 00:28:32.613
Oh, right.

00:28:32.613 --> 00:28:34.154
You said Maltese aren't very smart.

00:28:34.154 --> 00:28:36.571
Kongsoon isn't that smart either.

00:28:36.571 --> 00:28:39.071
She even gets lost sometimes.

00:28:39.071 --> 00:28:40.571
But...

00:28:40.571 --> 00:28:42.106
Maltese...

00:28:42.106 --> 00:28:43.529
Don't they eat poop?

00:28:43.529 --> 00:28:45.154
Oh, and...

00:28:45.154 --> 00:28:47.196
You said Maltese eat poop too.

00:28:47.196 --> 00:28:50.360
Kongsoon eats her own sometimes.

00:28:52.321 --> 00:28:54.571
But she's still really cute, right?

00:28:54.571 --> 00:28:56.904
I got her when I was in high school,

00:28:56.904 --> 00:28:59.663
and she's already thirteen.

00:29:02.084 --> 00:29:04.571
Usually when people see a dog,

00:29:04.571 --> 00:29:07.904
they talk about their own too, huh?

00:29:07.904 --> 00:29:09.238
When I'm at work,

00:29:09.238 --> 00:29:12.664
I don't really talk about personal things.

00:29:14.238 --> 00:29:17.105
That's impressive.

00:29:17.105 --> 00:29:18.154
What?

00:29:18.154 --> 00:29:20.551
It's a compliment.

00:29:22.196 --> 00:29:24.820
Doesn't sound like one.

00:29:25.404 --> 00:29:27.950
It is.

00:29:31.904 --> 00:29:34.337
Let's go.

00:29:45.196 --> 00:29:47.942
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

00:29:53.196 --> 00:29:56.154
You can keep that umbrella.

00:29:56.154 --> 00:29:58.516
It might rain again tomorrow.

00:29:59.196 --> 00:30:01.446
Okay.

00:30:01.446 --> 00:30:04.139
Get some rest.

00:30:17.613 --> 00:30:21.113
Now I get what kind of person Soon Rok is.

00:30:21.113 --> 00:30:23.071
He...

00:30:23.071 --> 00:30:25.263
only says what's true.

00:30:25.263 --> 00:30:27.113
If it's tricky, he just says nothing.

00:30:27.113 --> 00:30:28.904
If he says it, he means it.

00:30:28.904 --> 00:30:30.196
Right.

00:30:30.196 --> 00:30:31.571
So...

00:30:31.571 --> 00:30:33.613
when he said Yumi was cool,

00:30:33.613 --> 00:30:36.677
he meant it.

00:30:38.654 --> 00:30:40.679
Shin Soon Rok.

00:30:40.679 --> 00:30:43.997
He is turning this whole place upside down.

00:30:43.997 --> 00:30:46.697
He's trouble. Real trouble.

00:31:24.321 --> 00:31:26.154
Writer...

00:31:26.154 --> 00:31:28.196
Did you wait long?

00:31:28.196 --> 00:31:32.516
They were all sold out,
so I had to borrow one from the hotel.

00:31:34.529 --> 00:31:37.363
Did Writer Kim get back okay?

00:31:37.363 --> 00:31:40.154
- Yeah.
- Okay...

00:31:40.154 --> 00:31:42.988
That was seriously embarrassing earlier,

00:31:42.988 --> 00:31:44.154
but

00:31:44.154 --> 00:31:46.363
something just hit me.

00:31:46.363 --> 00:31:48.363
What?

00:31:48.363 --> 00:31:49.904
Inspiration.

00:31:49.904 --> 00:31:53.571
We were stuck on Ji Hoon
and Su Jeong's storyline,

00:31:53.571 --> 00:31:55.404
but after getting shut down like that,

00:31:55.404 --> 00:31:58.777
ideas just started pouring in.

00:31:58.777 --> 00:32:02.203
So I was writing it all down just now.

00:32:02.203 --> 00:32:04.123
- That's good.
- Yeah.

00:32:04.123 --> 00:32:06.446
At least I got something out of it.

00:32:06.446 --> 00:32:09.279
It wasn't a total waste.

00:32:09.279 --> 00:32:12.798
- Let's go.
- Yeah, let's go.

00:32:14.238 --> 00:32:16.654
But hey,

00:32:16.654 --> 00:32:19.960
something's been bugging me.

00:32:22.363 --> 00:32:25.529
What you said earlier...

00:32:25.529 --> 00:32:27.638
She hadn't even arrived yet, so why did you say

00:32:27.638 --> 00:32:31.631
she'd be watching the movie
and not to call her?

00:32:34.238 --> 00:32:38.844
That part stuck with me.

00:32:41.004 --> 00:32:42.029
Darn it.

00:32:42.029 --> 00:32:44.482
Another emergency!

00:32:45.504 --> 00:32:47.071
Name, Kim Ju Ho.

00:32:47.071 --> 00:32:48.738
Relationship, assigned writer.

00:32:48.738 --> 00:32:50.488
Priority, very high.

00:32:50.488 --> 00:32:52.196
Closeness, average.

00:32:52.196 --> 00:32:53.897
Affinity, very low.

00:32:53.897 --> 00:32:54.946
Focus.

00:32:54.946 --> 00:32:57.529
Priority is very high here.

00:32:57.529 --> 00:32:59.696
Hey, focus.

00:32:59.696 --> 00:33:02.354
Is he someone he can be honest with?

00:33:02.354 --> 00:33:03.529
No.

00:33:03.529 --> 00:33:07.000
Would being honest help the work?

00:33:09.666 --> 00:33:11.113
No.

00:33:11.113 --> 00:33:13.863
- Agreed.
- Exactly.

00:33:13.863 --> 00:33:15.946
Soon Rok's Principle three.

00:33:15.946 --> 00:33:20.113
If he can't be honest, he stays silent.

00:33:20.113 --> 00:33:23.639
I thought about why you said that,

00:33:24.446 --> 00:33:26.613
and it probably means
you don't like how I do things.

00:33:26.613 --> 00:33:28.821
Right?

00:33:28.821 --> 00:33:30.779
Like, "You pathetic writer."

00:33:30.779 --> 00:33:34.154
"Stop messing around and keep your mouth shut."

00:33:34.154 --> 00:33:36.374
Something like that, huh?

00:33:42.363 --> 00:33:44.613
So basically, you don't like me.

00:33:44.613 --> 00:33:46.904
Then

00:33:46.904 --> 00:33:49.446
if we think differently,

00:33:49.446 --> 00:33:51.071
do I have to adjust?

00:33:51.071 --> 00:33:54.319
Do I have to adjust to you?

00:33:58.196 --> 00:34:01.196
- No.
- Then what?

00:34:01.196 --> 00:34:05.102
Don't say anything, Soon Rok.

00:34:18.339 --> 00:34:20.325
Writer Kim.

00:34:25.363 --> 00:34:27.821
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah, did you?

00:34:27.821 --> 00:34:29.363
Yeah.

00:34:29.363 --> 00:34:32.196
I heard you went all the way to a fourth round.

00:34:32.196 --> 00:34:33.446
You're up early.

00:34:33.446 --> 00:34:35.854
I passed out and then got up.

00:34:36.821 --> 00:34:38.571
You look pretty refreshed.

00:34:38.571 --> 00:34:41.446
The sauna here is great.

00:34:41.446 --> 00:34:42.738
And for breakfast,

00:34:42.738 --> 00:34:44.196
I highly recommend the pho.

00:34:44.196 --> 00:34:46.492
It clears you right up.

00:34:46.492 --> 00:34:50.404
That's why you look so fresh.

00:34:50.404 --> 00:34:51.904
Would you like some coffee?

00:34:51.904 --> 00:34:53.605
Yes, please.

00:34:53.605 --> 00:34:56.063
A hot latte.

00:34:57.492 --> 00:35:00.223
I heard you watched a movie last night.

00:35:00.223 --> 00:35:02.738
Yeah.

00:35:02.738 --> 00:35:07.171
I'd been wanting to see it,
and it was the last showing.

00:35:07.171 --> 00:35:09.029
How did you know?

00:35:09.029 --> 00:35:11.363
You got in pretty late last night.

00:35:11.363 --> 00:35:12.888
I talked to Ju Ho.

00:35:12.888 --> 00:35:14.988
He already got on the train.

00:35:14.988 --> 00:35:17.404
Oh, he went back to Seoul?

00:35:17.404 --> 00:35:18.863
Yeah.

00:35:18.863 --> 00:35:21.404
No way it's because of Yumi.

00:35:21.404 --> 00:35:23.404
I see.

00:35:23.404 --> 00:35:24.738
But why so suddenly...

00:35:24.738 --> 00:35:26.147
He had an interview.

00:35:26.147 --> 00:35:27.779
It was already scheduled.

00:35:27.779 --> 00:35:30.502
Oh, okay.

00:35:30.502 --> 00:35:32.238
Good, that's a relief.

00:35:32.238 --> 00:35:34.321
So Soon Rok went too?

00:35:34.321 --> 00:35:35.488
Already?

00:35:35.488 --> 00:35:39.029
Then PD Shin went with him?

00:35:39.029 --> 00:35:40.863
No, he's in his room.

00:35:40.863 --> 00:35:43.446
He got soaked in the rain
and caught a bad cold.

00:35:43.446 --> 00:35:45.613
He's completely down.

00:35:45.613 --> 00:35:47.152
Oh no.

00:35:48.279 --> 00:35:50.980
By the way,

00:35:50.980 --> 00:35:53.477
- Yeah?
- last night...

00:35:57.404 --> 00:35:59.904
Oh, sorry, I should get going.

00:35:59.904 --> 00:36:01.529
Make sure you eat.

00:36:01.529 --> 00:36:02.863
Hello, sir.

00:36:02.863 --> 00:36:04.446
Yeah.

00:36:04.446 --> 00:36:06.321
What was that? That felt off.

00:36:06.321 --> 00:36:08.696
Yeah, something's off.

00:36:08.696 --> 00:36:12.769
Writer Kim Ju Ho left early this morning...

00:36:38.278 --> 00:36:40.147
Yes?

00:36:40.147 --> 00:36:41.196
Hello,

00:36:41.196 --> 00:36:44.349
it's Kim Yumi.

00:36:50.113 --> 00:36:52.071
Writer Kim?

00:36:52.071 --> 00:36:54.564
Are you okay? I heard you're sick.

00:36:55.529 --> 00:36:57.904
Yeah, just a bit of a cold.

00:36:57.904 --> 00:37:00.212
It's nothing serious.

00:37:02.238 --> 00:37:04.446
From the rain last night, right?

00:37:04.446 --> 00:37:06.154
Gosh...

00:37:06.154 --> 00:37:08.863
I'm fine. I took medicine.

00:37:10.321 --> 00:37:12.113
But

00:37:12.113 --> 00:37:14.571
did something happen?

00:37:14.571 --> 00:37:15.597
What?

00:37:15.597 --> 00:37:18.933
I heard Writer Kim Ju Ho left early.

00:37:19.696 --> 00:37:20.846
He had an interview.

00:37:20.846 --> 00:37:23.404
Didn't you go with him?

00:37:23.404 --> 00:37:25.087
Me?

00:37:27.696 --> 00:37:31.272
I didn't need to go anymore.

00:37:31.272 --> 00:37:32.321
What?

00:37:32.321 --> 00:37:33.946
I got cut.

00:37:33.946 --> 00:37:36.045
Yesterday.

00:37:51.855 --> 00:37:54.472
[Episode 15: Love X-Ray]

00:37:55.481 --> 00:37:58.488
You got cut from his team?

00:37:58.488 --> 00:38:00.105
Yesterday?

00:38:00.105 --> 00:38:01.745
Why all of a sudden?

00:38:02.488 --> 00:38:03.738
I guess

00:38:03.738 --> 00:38:06.279
he really was upset yesterday.

00:38:06.279 --> 00:38:08.363
It's because of me, right?

00:38:08.363 --> 00:38:11.313
- No.
- I think it is.

00:38:11.313 --> 00:38:12.363
No.

00:38:12.363 --> 00:38:15.233
- If not...
- Writer Kim.

00:38:16.117 --> 00:38:18.863
We're heading to Gamcheon Village today, right?

00:38:18.863 --> 00:38:21.154
That team leaves in ten minutes,

00:38:21.154 --> 00:38:23.230
- so please get ready.
- Okay, got it.

00:38:23.230 --> 00:38:26.696
PD Shin was supposed to lead, but he's sick.

00:38:26.696 --> 00:38:28.738
I'm sorry.

00:38:28.738 --> 00:38:31.321
PD Yoo will take that group.

00:38:31.321 --> 00:38:33.071
So please come to the lobby right away.

00:38:33.071 --> 00:38:34.498
Okay.

00:38:38.459 --> 00:38:39.613
- Then...
- Hello, it's me.

00:38:39.613 --> 00:38:41.571
Have a good trip.

00:38:41.571 --> 00:38:44.699
Thanks, get some rest.

00:38:49.688 --> 00:38:53.063
What is with that writer?

00:38:55.821 --> 00:38:57.363
Unbelievable, Kim Ju Ho.

00:38:57.363 --> 00:38:59.111
His pride got hurt?

00:38:59.111 --> 00:39:01.321
He couldn't say a word to Yumi,

00:39:01.321 --> 00:39:03.313
so why take it out on Soon Rok?

00:39:03.313 --> 00:39:06.605
We should just call him and say something.

00:39:08.988 --> 00:39:12.234
We can't just let this slide.

00:39:13.705 --> 00:39:16.375
Someone has to say something.

00:39:17.863 --> 00:39:19.821
This isn't right.

00:39:36.216 --> 00:39:37.738
Writer Kim, over here.

00:39:37.738 --> 00:39:39.363
- Hurry up.
- Just a second.

00:39:39.363 --> 00:39:40.571
Come on.

00:39:40.571 --> 00:39:42.196
Everyone's already on.

00:39:42.196 --> 00:39:44.613
- Come on, over here.
- Hello.

00:39:45.298 --> 00:39:48.327
- Take good care of them.
- Yeah.

00:39:48.327 --> 00:39:50.784
Have a good trip.

00:40:07.562 --> 00:40:09.239
Writer Kim.

00:40:09.239 --> 00:40:10.988
Did you sleep well?

00:40:10.988 --> 00:40:13.181
Yeah.

00:40:15.885 --> 00:40:18.110
By the way,

00:40:18.110 --> 00:40:21.651
did something happen with Writer Ju Ho?

00:40:21.651 --> 00:40:23.488
Why?

00:40:23.488 --> 00:40:25.779
He got seriously upset

00:40:25.779 --> 00:40:28.988
and went back to Seoul.

00:40:28.988 --> 00:40:30.618
He even cut PD Shin.

00:40:30.618 --> 00:40:31.654
What?

00:40:31.654 --> 00:40:35.446
That rumor spread fast.

00:40:35.446 --> 00:40:38.321
Where did you hear that?

00:40:38.321 --> 00:40:40.446
Who do you think?

00:40:40.446 --> 00:40:42.552
From him.

00:40:43.746 --> 00:40:45.071
He spent all night

00:40:45.071 --> 00:40:46.846
talking to Writer Yoon

00:40:46.846 --> 00:40:49.779
about PD Shin.

00:40:49.779 --> 00:40:52.196
He was upset at him.

00:40:52.196 --> 00:40:54.904
What did he say again...

00:40:54.904 --> 00:40:58.529
That he was arrogant or something.

00:40:58.529 --> 00:40:59.988
Ju Ho is

00:40:59.988 --> 00:41:02.355
always like that.

00:41:02.355 --> 00:41:03.446
That's why his nickname is

00:41:03.446 --> 00:41:06.509
Mr. Sensitive.

00:41:37.238 --> 00:41:39.279
Everyone, please move this way.

00:41:39.279 --> 00:41:40.363
- Okay.
- Yeah.

00:41:40.363 --> 00:41:42.946
Oh my God!

00:41:42.946 --> 00:41:45.472
This feels so freeing!

00:41:56.446 --> 00:41:58.321
- Excuse me, PD Yoo.
- Yes?

00:41:58.321 --> 00:42:01.139
Go ahead. I just need to make a quick call.

00:42:01.139 --> 00:42:02.571
Okay, just follow this path.

00:42:02.571 --> 00:42:05.182
- We'll go slowly.
- Okay.

00:42:11.878 --> 00:42:12.904
Hello?

00:42:12.904 --> 00:42:14.522
- Hello.
- Yeah.

00:42:14.522 --> 00:42:16.654
- Do you have a moment?
- Of course.

00:42:16.654 --> 00:42:18.113
Are you enjoying the trip?

00:42:18.113 --> 00:42:19.154
Yes.

00:42:19.154 --> 00:42:23.113
About what you were saying earlier...

00:42:23.113 --> 00:42:24.779
What I was saying?

00:42:24.779 --> 00:42:25.946
Yes, you asked

00:42:25.946 --> 00:42:30.196
if something happened last night.

00:42:30.196 --> 00:42:32.136
Oh, right.

00:42:35.279 --> 00:42:38.154
I heard the three of you went to a movie,

00:42:38.154 --> 00:42:41.279
so I thought you might know something.

00:42:41.279 --> 00:42:43.545
He really likes Soon Rok,

00:42:43.545 --> 00:42:45.696
but suddenly he said
he couldn't work with him anymore.

00:42:45.696 --> 00:42:49.014
Something about feeling disrespected.

00:42:49.014 --> 00:42:50.363
This morning?

00:42:50.363 --> 00:42:52.096
Yes, he called out of nowhere.

00:42:52.096 --> 00:42:54.113
It caught me off guard too.

00:42:54.113 --> 00:42:56.955
And PD Shin won't say a word.

00:42:56.955 --> 00:43:00.772
I don't know
if something happened after drinking...

00:43:00.772 --> 00:43:03.972
Actually, something did happen.

00:43:05.488 --> 00:43:06.988
What happened?

00:43:06.988 --> 00:43:08.946
But honestly,

00:43:08.946 --> 00:43:12.029
it's just so childish.

00:43:12.029 --> 00:43:14.904
I'd rather not say it myself.

00:43:14.904 --> 00:43:18.097
It might be better
to hear it from him directly.

00:43:19.484 --> 00:43:21.654
Childish?

00:43:21.654 --> 00:43:24.274
Yes, really childish.

00:43:29.011 --> 00:43:30.029
Well,

00:43:30.029 --> 00:43:31.779
he can be childish.

00:43:31.779 --> 00:43:34.699
But that's kind of his charm too.

00:43:34.699 --> 00:43:36.863
That's not charming to everyone.

00:43:36.863 --> 00:43:38.779
Even on a first meeting?

00:43:38.779 --> 00:43:40.429
Oh, well...

00:43:40.429 --> 00:43:42.696
No, that's not okay for a first meeting.

00:43:42.696 --> 00:43:44.289
Anyway,

00:43:44.289 --> 00:43:47.071
I feel really bad for PD Shin.

00:43:47.071 --> 00:43:48.988
This doesn't feel right.

00:43:48.988 --> 00:43:51.868
I was hoping you could help resolve it.

00:43:53.696 --> 00:43:55.938
Then...

00:43:56.988 --> 00:43:58.321
what if

00:43:58.321 --> 00:44:02.529
PD Shin joins your team again?

00:44:02.529 --> 00:44:04.071
- What?
- I mean...

00:44:04.071 --> 00:44:06.904
You said you felt sorry for Soon Rok,

00:44:06.904 --> 00:44:09.738
so I just thought I'd suggest it.

00:44:09.738 --> 00:44:11.177
Say yes.

00:44:11.177 --> 00:44:13.184
Say yes!

00:44:15.614 --> 00:44:17.363
That would be fine.

00:44:17.363 --> 00:44:19.331
I'm okay with it.

00:44:19.331 --> 00:44:20.946
Really?

00:44:20.946 --> 00:44:22.571
Yes.

00:44:22.571 --> 00:44:25.654
It was just a scheduling issue before, right?

00:44:25.654 --> 00:44:29.571
I actually liked PD Shin's feedback.

00:44:29.571 --> 00:44:31.738
Great, great.

00:44:31.738 --> 00:44:32.988
But

00:44:32.988 --> 00:44:35.421
his opinion matters too.

00:44:35.421 --> 00:44:37.230
Do we really need to hear it?

00:44:37.230 --> 00:44:39.904
He caused trouble,
so he should just go along with it.

00:44:39.904 --> 00:44:41.710
That's a bit...

00:44:41.710 --> 00:44:43.571
I'll talk to him

00:44:43.571 --> 00:44:44.946
when I get back.

00:44:44.946 --> 00:44:46.654
Alright, thank you.

00:44:46.654 --> 00:44:48.686
Yeah.

00:44:52.616 --> 00:44:54.462
Oh...

00:44:55.321 --> 00:44:57.974
Is this really happening?

00:45:00.295 --> 00:45:03.129
Is this a good thing?

00:45:03.129 --> 00:45:04.821
It is!

00:45:15.654 --> 00:45:16.904
Guys,

00:45:16.904 --> 00:45:19.444
Soon Rok is coming back.

00:45:23.238 --> 00:45:25.988
Let's have meetings every day when he's back.

00:45:25.988 --> 00:45:29.506
Then we'll see him every day!

00:45:30.727 --> 00:45:31.755
Are you crazy?

00:45:31.755 --> 00:45:32.988
Writers don't just sit in meetings.

00:45:32.988 --> 00:45:34.813
They're supposed to write!

00:45:34.813 --> 00:45:36.946
That's not my concern.

00:45:36.946 --> 00:45:40.596
I'm just really happy right now.

00:45:42.918 --> 00:45:44.855
Well, yeah.

00:45:44.855 --> 00:45:46.839
I guess it worked out.

00:45:47.863 --> 00:45:50.071
Maybe you should tell Soon Rok.

00:45:50.071 --> 00:45:52.363
It'd be weird if he hears it from the editor.

00:45:52.363 --> 00:45:54.189
Yeah.

00:46:05.279 --> 00:46:07.488
Why isn't he picking up?

00:46:07.488 --> 00:46:09.529
- The call cannot be completed.
- Writer Kim!

00:46:09.529 --> 00:46:10.946
Everyone's waiting.

00:46:10.946 --> 00:46:13.547
Okay, coming.

00:46:13.547 --> 00:46:15.312
Amazing.

00:46:15.312 --> 00:46:17.071
- We should take pictures here.
- Sounds good.

00:46:17.071 --> 00:46:18.829
- Everyone, gather up.
- Okay.

00:46:18.829 --> 00:46:20.446
Writer Kim, over here.

00:46:20.446 --> 00:46:22.738
- Stand in the best spot.
- No, I'm fine.

00:46:22.738 --> 00:46:24.821
- Come on over.
- Thank you.

00:46:24.821 --> 00:46:27.263
Let's do heart poses today.

00:46:27.263 --> 00:46:29.613
- Sounds good.
- One, two, three.

00:46:29.613 --> 00:46:30.696
Heart.

00:46:30.696 --> 00:46:32.988
That's really pretty.

00:46:32.988 --> 00:46:35.113
The colors are so nice.

00:46:35.113 --> 00:46:36.529
This view is incredible.

00:46:36.529 --> 00:46:39.113
Every house is a different color.

00:46:39.113 --> 00:46:41.766
One, two, three.

00:46:54.821 --> 00:46:57.315
Why isn't he calling?

00:47:15.857 --> 00:47:18.777
Busan is stunning!

00:47:19.613 --> 00:47:21.946
Would you two like to head
to the restaurant on your own?

00:47:21.946 --> 00:47:23.404
I'm a bit hot,

00:47:23.404 --> 00:47:26.488
so I'll grab an iced Americano
and cool off first.

00:47:26.488 --> 00:47:28.863
I've been sweating so much.

00:47:28.863 --> 00:47:31.196
Is it okay if I skip it?

00:47:31.196 --> 00:47:34.188
I ate too much this morning,
so I'm not really hungry.

00:47:34.188 --> 00:47:35.252
Of course.

00:47:35.252 --> 00:47:37.779
We have dinner plans later anyway.

00:47:37.779 --> 00:47:39.238
Then we'll head over first.

00:47:39.238 --> 00:47:41.113
- Okay.
- Yeah.

00:47:41.113 --> 00:47:43.319
Want to grab a drink?

00:48:08.934 --> 00:48:12.388
Am I waking him up for nothing?

00:48:15.712 --> 00:48:17.772
PD Shin, how are you feeling...

00:48:17.772 --> 00:48:19.946
Excuse me,

00:48:19.946 --> 00:48:23.914
are you with the guest in room 410?

00:48:23.914 --> 00:48:25.238
Yes.

00:48:25.238 --> 00:48:27.571
Is the young man okay?

00:48:27.571 --> 00:48:29.290
Sorry?

00:48:29.290 --> 00:48:30.821
What do you mean?

00:48:30.821 --> 00:48:33.529
He was very sick earlier
and went to the hospital.

00:48:33.529 --> 00:48:35.355
I was wondering if he's okay now.

00:48:35.355 --> 00:48:36.404
What?

00:48:36.404 --> 00:48:40.757
I recommended a nearby clinic.

00:48:42.120 --> 00:48:44.558
Where is it?

00:48:50.950 --> 00:48:53.063
All set.

00:48:54.547 --> 00:48:56.547
Welcome.

00:48:56.547 --> 00:48:59.571
Has someone named Shin Soon Rok come in?

00:48:59.571 --> 00:49:00.654
Shin Soon Rok?

00:49:00.654 --> 00:49:02.363
Yes, could you check?

00:49:02.363 --> 00:49:04.431
Sure.

00:49:12.154 --> 00:49:14.321
He had a high fever, so he's on an IV.

00:49:14.321 --> 00:49:16.514
I see.

00:50:00.927 --> 00:50:04.274
I just wanted to check if your fever went down.

00:50:04.896 --> 00:50:08.246
The nurse said it was really high.

00:50:10.196 --> 00:50:12.949
It seems a lot better now, thankfully.

00:50:14.071 --> 00:50:16.738
How did you find this place?

00:50:16.738 --> 00:50:19.238
The hotel staff told me.

00:50:19.238 --> 00:50:21.779
I was worried when I couldn't reach you.

00:50:21.779 --> 00:50:23.863
Weren't you at Gamcheon Village earlier?

00:50:23.863 --> 00:50:26.238
I already went.

00:50:29.154 --> 00:50:31.472
One moment please.

00:50:32.821 --> 00:50:34.238
- I'll remove the IV now.
- Okay.

00:50:34.238 --> 00:50:36.136
I'll wait outside.

00:50:45.886 --> 00:50:46.938
All done.

00:50:46.938 --> 00:50:48.272
Thank you.

00:51:29.238 --> 00:51:31.566
I knew this would happen.

00:51:36.246 --> 00:51:37.279
What are you doing?

00:51:37.279 --> 00:51:39.847
It's flaring up again.

00:51:40.914 --> 00:51:42.238
It's not me.

00:51:42.238 --> 00:51:44.558
I was asleep.

00:51:46.029 --> 00:51:48.738
I told you, it wasn't me.

00:51:48.738 --> 00:51:51.238
Right, it wasn't you.

00:51:51.238 --> 00:51:52.821
It was Writer Kim.

00:51:52.821 --> 00:51:53.904
What?

00:51:53.904 --> 00:51:57.238
She's the one who asked to watch the movie.

00:51:57.238 --> 00:51:59.404
She's the one who wanted to share the umbrella.

00:51:59.404 --> 00:52:01.863
She's the one who touched his forehead.

00:52:01.863 --> 00:52:04.159
See? It wasn't me.

00:52:04.159 --> 00:52:06.712
We need to see Love Cell.

00:52:14.240 --> 00:52:16.167
Love Cell.

00:52:17.788 --> 00:52:19.744
Soon Rok's Love Cell

00:52:19.744 --> 00:52:22.946
is a renowned surgeon.

00:52:22.946 --> 00:52:25.503
Is this a photo of Writer Kim?

00:52:25.503 --> 00:52:26.529
Yeah.

00:52:26.529 --> 00:52:29.571
You're great at reading X-rays, right?

00:52:29.571 --> 00:52:32.857
Take a look at her feelings.

00:52:36.213 --> 00:52:37.488
What do you see?

00:52:37.488 --> 00:52:40.363
See this here?

00:52:40.363 --> 00:52:42.441
It looks like a heart.

00:52:43.863 --> 00:52:45.363
What is that?

00:52:45.363 --> 00:52:47.238
Wait, is it a tumor?

00:52:47.238 --> 00:52:48.902
No.

00:52:50.105 --> 00:52:53.191
It's a love X-ray!

00:52:56.738 --> 00:53:00.613
This is a compound of interest and curiosity.

00:53:00.613 --> 00:53:03.029
Interest and curiosity?

00:53:03.029 --> 00:53:04.529
It's still in the early stage.

00:53:04.529 --> 00:53:06.863
But if it keeps growing,

00:53:06.863 --> 00:53:08.275
it turns into love.

00:53:08.275 --> 00:53:11.095
Then what should Soon Rok do?

00:53:20.029 --> 00:53:21.904
If he accepts her feelings,

00:53:21.904 --> 00:53:24.154
that's when a relationship begins.

00:53:24.154 --> 00:53:28.417
But he doesn't date within work relationships.

00:53:30.647 --> 00:53:32.624
[Ongyeol Internal Medicine Clinic]

00:53:37.988 --> 00:53:40.081
Wait long?

00:53:40.901 --> 00:53:42.196
Are you okay?

00:53:42.196 --> 00:53:43.738
Yeah, I'm fine.

00:53:43.738 --> 00:53:45.562
I feel much better.

00:53:45.562 --> 00:53:48.419
I picked up the meds.

00:53:48.419 --> 00:53:51.630
Oh, thanks.

00:53:51.630 --> 00:53:53.238
Let's grab lunch.

00:53:53.238 --> 00:53:56.279
There's a porridge place nearby
with good reviews.

00:53:56.279 --> 00:53:58.002
Well, I'm not really hungry.

00:53:58.002 --> 00:54:00.238
You need to eat to take your meds.

00:54:00.238 --> 00:54:02.928
And I'm hungry too.

00:54:04.529 --> 00:54:07.484
I'll treat. Let's go.

00:54:16.044 --> 00:54:17.696
They say this place is good.

00:54:17.696 --> 00:54:21.071
Apparently not all porridge is the same.

00:54:21.071 --> 00:54:23.571
Looks legit.

00:54:23.571 --> 00:54:27.029
You've been through a lot since yesterday
because of me.

00:54:27.029 --> 00:54:28.761
Not at all.

00:54:29.988 --> 00:54:32.904
What will you be working on
once you're back in Seoul?

00:54:32.904 --> 00:54:35.488
Since you're off Writer Ju Ho's team...

00:54:35.488 --> 00:54:36.613
I'm not sure.

00:54:36.613 --> 00:54:38.738
I'll hand things over first.

00:54:38.738 --> 00:54:41.709
Probably stay in-office for a while.

00:54:41.709 --> 00:54:44.029
Stuff like overseas rights

00:54:44.029 --> 00:54:47.035
and tedious paperwork.

00:54:49.154 --> 00:54:50.654
Come back

00:54:50.654 --> 00:54:52.988
on my project.

00:54:52.988 --> 00:54:55.196
You only stepped off because of scheduling.

00:54:55.196 --> 00:54:56.855
Now that it's sorted,

00:54:56.855 --> 00:55:00.522
it makes sense for you to rejoin, right?

00:55:02.363 --> 00:55:04.571
That's not really my call.

00:55:04.571 --> 00:55:07.321
Then I'll talk to the editor

00:55:07.321 --> 00:55:10.091
and decide from there.

00:55:12.321 --> 00:55:15.691
Alright, we'll talk it over.

00:55:17.106 --> 00:55:19.779
Nice. Cool and professional.

00:55:19.779 --> 00:55:22.785
You didn't show a thing.

00:55:26.488 --> 00:55:29.321
Join her team again?

00:55:29.321 --> 00:55:30.904
What should you do?

00:55:30.904 --> 00:55:32.613
It'd be good for him.

00:55:32.613 --> 00:55:35.446
He likes her writing.

00:55:35.446 --> 00:55:37.154
And she's a good person.

00:55:37.154 --> 00:55:38.654
Not like Kim Ju Ho.

00:55:38.654 --> 00:55:41.207
Then what about this?

00:55:42.337 --> 00:55:44.988
Accept it or not?

00:55:44.988 --> 00:55:48.238
He doesn't date at work.

00:55:48.238 --> 00:55:49.946
He doesn't want to mess things up.

00:55:49.946 --> 00:55:52.446
And he hates complications.

00:55:52.446 --> 00:55:55.121
Then let's cut it off now.

00:55:56.439 --> 00:55:59.605
Before it gets bigger.

00:56:02.335 --> 00:56:05.429
[Surgery in progress]

00:56:16.571 --> 00:56:19.188
Starting the procedure.

00:56:19.188 --> 00:56:20.231
Scalpel!

00:56:20.231 --> 00:56:21.622
Scalpel.

00:56:23.404 --> 00:56:25.529
It might hurt her,

00:56:25.529 --> 00:56:28.104
but this is the best way.

00:56:30.904 --> 00:56:32.404
Enjoy your meal.

00:56:32.404 --> 00:56:33.571
Thank you.

00:56:33.571 --> 00:56:35.953
That's a lot.

00:56:35.953 --> 00:56:38.366
I've got it.

00:56:44.154 --> 00:56:47.071
- Hello?
- Where are you?

00:56:47.071 --> 00:56:49.738
Just left the hospital.

00:56:49.738 --> 00:56:52.988
Having lunch with Writer Kim.

00:56:52.988 --> 00:56:55.779
She came early too.

00:56:55.779 --> 00:56:57.738
About 30 minutes?

00:57:00.946 --> 00:57:03.238
Yeah, I'll eat and head back.

00:57:03.238 --> 00:57:05.071
Okay.

00:57:05.071 --> 00:57:06.529
Oh, by the way.

00:57:06.529 --> 00:57:08.821
About what you mentioned.

00:57:08.821 --> 00:57:11.154
That plan.

00:57:11.154 --> 00:57:15.194
- Can you set it up?
- Oh, you're going through with it?

00:57:21.113 --> 00:57:24.238
I just... changed my mind.

00:57:24.238 --> 00:57:26.696
I'll try to fit it into my schedule.

00:57:26.696 --> 00:57:28.742
Okay.

00:57:30.564 --> 00:57:32.113
That was PD Jang.

00:57:32.113 --> 00:57:34.804
Their team just got back to the hotel.

00:57:35.654 --> 00:57:39.425
What kind of plan was that?
Her voice got so excited.

00:57:39.425 --> 00:57:42.145
I could hear it.

00:57:43.029 --> 00:57:45.442
A blind date.

00:57:45.442 --> 00:57:47.488
I kept turning them down because I was busy,

00:57:47.488 --> 00:57:51.068
but now I've got time, so I figured why not.

00:57:57.113 --> 00:57:58.138
I didn't know

00:57:58.138 --> 00:58:02.446
you went on blind dates.

00:58:02.446 --> 00:58:04.654
I'm not exactly against them.

00:58:04.654 --> 00:58:07.340
I see.

00:58:10.571 --> 00:58:12.397
Hope it goes well.

00:58:14.946 --> 00:58:17.178
Do you know anyone?

00:58:18.196 --> 00:58:19.238
Who?

00:58:19.238 --> 00:58:22.178
Someone who could set me up.

00:58:22.936 --> 00:58:25.154
The one on the receiving end knows.

00:58:25.154 --> 00:58:28.907
He's drawing a line.

00:58:34.279 --> 00:58:36.488
So it hurts,

00:58:36.488 --> 00:58:38.673
but it can't be helped.

00:58:45.113 --> 00:58:47.886
I'll look into it.

00:58:49.071 --> 00:58:50.587
Okay.

00:58:55.696 --> 00:58:57.477
This is good.

00:59:17.321 --> 00:59:18.904
Thanks for today.

00:59:18.904 --> 00:59:21.571
Get some rest,
and make sure you take your meds.

00:59:21.571 --> 00:59:23.079
Okay.

00:59:47.321 --> 00:59:51.456
Good. Looks like the surgery was a success.

01:00:08.404 --> 01:00:10.904
This workshop was a mess.

01:00:10.904 --> 01:00:12.488
Broke all the rules.

01:00:12.488 --> 01:00:14.863
No boundaries between work and personal.

01:00:14.863 --> 01:00:18.470
Let's not let that happen again.

01:00:42.337 --> 01:00:44.071
- Good work.
- Yeah.

01:00:44.071 --> 01:00:46.769
Let's get some rest.

01:00:53.980 --> 01:00:55.238
What's this?

01:00:55.238 --> 01:00:58.079
There's another photo.

01:00:58.079 --> 01:00:59.548
Wait.

01:01:00.238 --> 01:01:03.181
This isn't the one we removed.

01:01:03.181 --> 01:01:04.943
What is this?

01:01:06.119 --> 01:01:08.298
How come...

01:01:21.279 --> 01:01:25.139
I just thought of someone. A junior I know.

01:01:26.363 --> 01:01:28.238
I think she'd be a great match for you.

01:01:28.238 --> 01:01:30.596
Want to meet her?

01:01:46.871 --> 01:01:50.354
That's not Writer Kim's photo, is it?

01:01:50.354 --> 01:01:52.240
[Shin Soon Rok]

01:01:53.154 --> 01:01:55.972
This is his photo!

01:02:29.821 --> 01:02:31.196
Are you still at your studio?

01:02:31.196 --> 01:02:33.961
If things aren't going well,
feel free to reach out anytime.

01:02:33.961 --> 01:02:36.779
I'm terrible at games.

01:02:36.779 --> 01:02:38.321
I've got plans.

01:02:38.321 --> 01:02:40.029
- Good luck.
- Today's Sunday...

01:02:40.029 --> 01:02:42.113
It's his blind date day.

01:02:42.113 --> 01:02:43.904
How did it go?

01:02:43.904 --> 01:02:45.904
She even called to wish him luck...

01:02:45.904 --> 01:02:47.696
Was drawing that line really necessary?

01:02:47.696 --> 01:02:50.154
Did you reach out to Jenny?

01:02:50.154 --> 01:02:51.946
Do I really have to?

01:02:51.946 --> 01:02:54.748
Isn't that PD Shin over there?